%N A394668 Number of partitions of n^2 into prime parts.
%F A394668 a(n) = A000607(n^2).
%e A394668 For n = 2, a(2) = 1 because n^2 = 4 can be partitioned into primes in exactly 1 way:
%e A394668   4 = 2 + 2.
%e A394668 For n = 3, a(3) = 4 because n^2 = 9 has exactly 4 partitions into prime parts:
%e A394668   9 = 7 + 2, 9 = 5 + 2 + 2, 9 = 3 + 3 + 3, 9 = 3 + 2 + 2 + 2.
%Y A394668 Cf. A000290. Subsequence of A000607.
